These are known security problems that cluster_install_XX.YY.sh creates.

* Passwordless ssh as user "root" and as user "scidb" are setup between the local machine you are running this cluster install from. Additionally this ssh is run with StrictHostKeyChecking=no.

* Passwordless ssh as user "root" and as user "scidb" are setup between the coordinator host and the rest of the hosts.

* Iptables are disabled.

* On CentOS/RH if the SELinux policy is Enabled you will have problems with ssh.

* The virbr0 network interface is shutdown.

* User scidb's .bashrc file is modified.
